<h2 id="gaming-time-and-comment-data"><span class="prefix"></span><span class="content">Gaming Time and Comment Data</span><span class="suffix"></span></h2>
<p>  With the expansion of computer storage capacity and processing speed, gaming systems can track and record players’ playing time more accurately. Thus, gaming time data and comment data are born at the right moment.<br>
   The game developers would need such data very much. The game developer could check the time that players spend on each game mode which reflects which part is highly welcomed, making him understand the tastes of players. Also, the comment data directly reflect the shortcoming existing in current version which are discovered my the players. All the data could help the developers develop the strong points and overcome shortcomings in next version.<br>
   There’re multiple resources we could browse. Take Tom Clancy’s Rainbow Six Siege for example.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://howlongtobeat.com/">HowLongToBeat</a>:Using this website, we could intuitively see the average, most and least time players spending on every mode. Also, there are plenty of comments.<br>
<img alt="输入图片说明" src="data:image/png;base64,"><br>
<img alt="输入图片说明" src="data:image/png;base64,"></li>
<li><a href="https://newzoo.com/">Newzoo</a>:This is a professional website used for financial purpose, and it is much more visual.<img alt="输入图片说明" src="data:image/png;base64,"><br>
   There’re many ways to get the data.<br>
    1. We could download the data from the website above.<br>
    2. Legally crawling data from the website.<br>
    3. A clumsy way: issue a questionnaire to collect some data.<br>
   As a result, we successfully obtained the data of multiple games. Here just take R6 for example. We could see that in Single-player part time on main story is apparently less than other mode. Meanwhile, in Multi-Player part, competitive mode is more welcomed than cooperative mode. Thus, the developer could add more innovative elements in main story and cooperative mode, so that the game could catch more players’ heart.</li>
</ul>
